class WeatherControlSystem {
    private int temperature;
    private boolean acOn;
    private boolean heaterOn;

    public WeatherControlSystem() {
        this.temperature = 70; // Fahrenheit
        acOn = false;
        heaterOn = false;
    }

    public void adjustTemperature(int desiredTemp) {
        if (desiredTemp > temperature) {
            heaterOn = true;
            acOn = false;
        } else if (desiredTemp < temperature) {
            acOn = true;
            heaterOn = false;
        } else {
            acOn = false;
            heaterOn = false;
        }
        this.temperature = desiredTemp;
    }
}
",

If an external method sets `heaterOn` to true directly, without changing `desiredTemp`, will the `temperature` necessarily rise to reflect this change?
